<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3954687>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Indian Brachinus species: a) B. dryas Andrewes, 1936 (holotype, BMNH); b) B. inops Andrewes, 1932 (holotype, BMNH); c) B. hexagrammus Chaudoir, 1876 (syntype, MNHN); d) B. sexmaculatus Dejean, 1825 (syntype, MNHN); e) B. tetracolon Chuadoir, 1876 (syntype, MNHN); f) B. tetragrammus Chaudoir, 1876 (syntype, MNHN); g) B. pictus (Hope, 1833) (ZSIM); h) B. cinctellus Chaudoir, 1876 (syntype, MNHN); i) B. eucosmus Andrewes, 1937 (holotype, BMNH)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3954687/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3954695>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Morphological features of Brachinus: a) Elytral apex forming re-entrant angle; b) Elytral apex not forming a reentrant angle; c) Pronotum with apical margin having anterior projection on lateral sides, hind angles slightly acute; d) Pronotal apical margin without anterior projection on lateral sides, hind angles obtuse; e) Pronotum with hind angles acute; f) Pronotum with hind angle at right angles." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3954695/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

